e data structure, or use some previously banked credit.\n\n\n\n\nIf the credit invariant:\n\n\n\n\ncredit > 0 for all points in all sequences of operations\n\n\n\n\nis maintained, then the true cost of all sequences of operations is upper-bounded by the sum of the costs assigned to each operation.\n\n\n\n\nIn particular, since we normally assign O(1) costs, this can provide a good O(1) bound on a set of operations.", "updatedAt": 1714593321932}